{"id":14880908,"mediaExerciseId":"55524fc0-294a-4cca-ab5d-ef84428ddeb5","exerciseName":"10","chapterName":"5","chapterTitle":"Introduction to Valuation:The Time Value of Money","groupId":612293,"groupTitle":"Questions and Problems","isPremium":true,"sectionName":null,"sectionTitle":null,"pageNumber":147,"solutions":[{"id":6064120,"modifiedOn":"2021-01-01T00:00:00.000000","steps":[{"columns":[{"text":"In this exercise, we must determine the present worth of liability. ","images":{"latex":null,"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":true}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":1},{"columns":[{"text":"Imprudential, Inc has an unfunded pension liability that needs to be paid in 20 years. To assess the value of the stock they want to discount it to the present. here we need to calculate the present value of this liability. ","images":{"latex":null,"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":true}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":2},{"columns":[{"text":"We know the following data:\n\n|Imprudential, Inc||\n|--|--|\nLiabilities future value\t|$415 Million\nt\t|20\nDiscount rate|\t5.20%","images":{"latex":null,"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":3},{"columns":[{"text":"To calculate the Present Value (PV) of the liability we are going to use the formula of PV to discount the value of the liability in 20 years.\n\n$$ PV = \\frac{FV}{(1+r)^t} $$\n\n*Where:*\n- FV is the future value\n- r is the applied rate\n- t is the periods of time the rate is applied\n","images":{"latex":null,"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":4},{"columns":[{"text":"Now we need to compute the formula with the given data to obtain the PV.\n\n$$ \\begin{aligned}\nPV &= \\frac{\\$415}{(1+0.052)^{20}} \\\\\n\\\\\n& = \\boxed{\\$150.57}\n\\end{aligned}$$\n\nThe present value of the liability is of **$150.57** million.","images":{"latex":null,"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":5},{"columns":[{"text":"$150.57 million","images":{"latex":null,"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":true,"stepNumber":6}],"rating":0,"solutionUuid":"bdeca014-7dac-434b-9374-241416cae460","editorVersion":2,"answeredOn":null,"ratingCount":null,"solutionOrder":null,"totalSteps":6}],"textbook":{"authors":"Bradford D. Jordan, Randolph W. Westerfield, Stephen A. Ross","imageUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/textbook_covers/tmpm0p82b7h","imageThumbnailUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/cache/d1/d3/d1d34d106dd29dd2e71be582412ef59d.jpg","id":34320,"isbn":"9781259918957","isPremium":true,"title":"Fundamentals of Corporate Finance","edition":"12th Edition","verifiedSolutionCount":1217,"shouldBeIndexableForSeo":true,"modified":1665448474394,"active":true,"publisher":"McGraw-Hill Education","mainTextbookIsbn":null,"subjects":{"level1":["Social Science"],"level2":["Economics"],"level3":["Finance"]}},"nextExercises":[{"id":14880909,"exerciseName":"11","page":148,"hasSolution":true,"mediaExerciseId":"2cfbfa68-f899-4ea7-8efa-54ee33dab024","_webUrl":"https://quizlet.com/explanations/textbook-solutions/fundamentals-of-corporate-finance-12th-edition-9781259918957/chapter-5-questions-and-problems-11-2cfbfa68-f899-4ea7-8efa-54ee33dab024"},{"id":14880910,"exerciseName":"12","page":148,"hasSolution":true,"mediaExerciseId":"a66bba91-d91b-46d2-a664-5a51b9fd5884","_webUrl":"https://quizlet.com/explanations/textbook-solutions/fundamentals-of-corporate-finance-12th-edition-9781259918957/chapter-5-questions-and-problems-12-a66bba91-d91b-46d2-a664-5a51b9fd5884"}],"previousExercises":[{"id":14880907,"exerciseName":"9","page":147,"hasSolution":true,"mediaExerciseId":"b239f356-10e9-4fbd-81d8-876a76318bfe","_webUrl":"https://quizlet.com/explanations/textbook-solutions/fundamentals-of-corporate-finance-12th-edition-9781259918957/chapter-5-questions-and-problems-9-b239f356-10e9-4fbd-81d8-8